headline: A Web of Loose Ends to Pull, or Look Past
abstract: Recent interviews by Lev Parnas, an associate of the president’s personal lawyer, as well as documents released by House investigators, reinforced that there is more still to be learned.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — By the time the Senate opened impeachment trials for Andrew Johnson and Bill Clinton, its members pretty well knew the facts of the accusations against the presidents. None of them needed to turn on “The Rachel Maddow Show” to learn things they did not already know.
keywords: Trump-Ukraine Whistle-blower Complaint and Impeachment Inquiry
